{"questionListItems":[{"id":"cluhz8np900a7124ysnemvq9g","title":"Can I have a remediation session?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np900a8124y6siiihez","body":"If you have signed a settlement agreement through a CMC mediation, you can request for a remediation if there is a breach of agreement or you wish to discuss new terms. Please call the Minlaw Enquiry Line at 1800 2255 529 during office hours to request for a remediation. If your last mediation is less than 3 months ago, you are not required to pay any fees.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np900a9124ys2dxiqjn","title":"Where is the CMC mediation at?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np900aa124ymhi2plxc","body":"The CMC mediations are held at 45 Maxwell Road, The URA Centre (East Wing), #07-11, Singapore 069118.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np900ab124y7x7rmrmi","title":"I have received a letter of invitation to mediate from the CMC. What do I do ?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np900ac124ycyt5xjxa","body":"Please call the Minlaw Enquiry Line at 1800 2255 529 during office hours and inform them whether you would like to accept or decline the invitation. Alternatively, you can submit your response via the online form at https://eservices.mlaw.gov.sg/enquiry/<a href=\"http://www.mlaw.gov.sg/eservices/enquiry/\" target=\"_blank\"></a>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np900ad124yu82xil0l","title":"Can CMC send someone to investigate into my complaints?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np900ae124y4xoz5uod","body":"The CMC does not not have any investigative powers.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np900af124yrk90nxzk","title":"As a public offcer, how do I refer a case?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np900ag124yl0iql8v3","body":"<div>If you are representative from an agency, you can refer a case to the CMC through one the following modes: </div><div>                                                                1. By calling the Minlaw Enquiry Line at 1800 2255 529 during office hours </div><div>                                                                                               2. Submitting an online application that is available on CMC's website                                        </div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np900ah124yf8cfqve4","title":"What happens on the day of court referred mediation?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np900ai124y7z3ewf0c","body":"You will be required to report at the CMC at least 20 minutes before the mediation session. Please register at the appointment kiosk where a queue number will be issued and you will be directed to the mediation room indicated in your queue ticket. You are required to bring along their your NRIC/Passport/Work Pass as proof of your identification before the start of the session. The CMC staff will get you to sign a document to ensure that you understand that CMC mediation is governed by the CMC Act and is confidential. You will then brought into the mediation room.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np900aj124ycnm34f55","title":"What happens after I apply for mediation?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np900ak124y15o2f5pw","body":"After you have applied for mediation, you will receive a reply from the CMC within 3 working days, informing you on whether your application is accepted  or not. If it is accepted, the CMC will write to the person that you wish to have mediation with. If the person accepts the invitation, we will contact you for a mediation date and time. If the person declines or fails to respond, we will inform you accordingly.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8np900al124ywymsc0p6","title":"Does CMC accept disputes between residents in a condo?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8np900am124yvomvnihq","body":"<div>You can use CMC's mediation service to mediate any social, relational or community issues with your neighbour, regardless of whether you are staying in a public housing or private housing. Types of neighbour disputes that are suitable for the CMC mediation include </div><div> </div><div>                                                                                        1.  Activities that generate unacceptable smell </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                2. Activities that generate excessive smoke </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                     3. Animal related complaints </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               4. Causing damage to property </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           5. Display of unacceptable behaviour or conduct </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                          6. Dripping of water from laundry or other sources </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                      7. Littering </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                8. Misuse or obstruction of common property </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                9. Noise generated from activities done within a residence </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                       10. Noise generated from activities outside a place of residence </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                             11. Utterance of unacceptable words </div><div> </div><div>                                                                                                                                                                                                                             You can apply for mediation during office hours by calling the MINLAW Enquiry Line at 1800 2255 529 or apply online at the CMC website www.cmc.mlaw.gov.sg. You will need your Singpass to access this e-service</div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8npa00an124y0lvpbfza","title":"Can I request for counselling?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8npa00ao124ydfvxwb56","body":"The CMC does not provide counselling service. You may wish to approach the nearest Family Service Centre in your area of residence for assistance.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8npa00ap124y3fdq01l7","title":"When should I go to the CDRT?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8npa00aq124y5wug2tmo","body":"You can approach the CDRT if you wish to file a claim against your neighbour for unreasonable inteference with your enjoyment or use of your place of residence. For more information, please contact the State Courts at 1800 587 8423 or visit their website at www.statecourts.gov.sg for detailed and up to date information.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8npa00ar124yyks59c2r","title":"What can I do if I have a dispute with my main tenant?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8npa00as124y9vomuew0","body":"<div>If the issue that you have is not covered by a tenancy agreement, you can use CMC's mediation service to mediate the issues that are causing you concern. The following disputes are suitable for mediation:</div><div> </div><div> 1. Disagreement on living arrangements </div><div>2. Display of unacceptable behaviour or conduct </div><div> 3. Interest free monetary matter based on verbal agreement for amount involving less than $5000 </div><div>4. Problems with rented property or shared tenancy expenses </div><div>5. Refund of rental deposit </div><div>6.  Utterance of unacceptable words. </div><div> </div><div>You can apply for mediation during office hours by calling the MINLAW Enquiry Line at 1800 2255 529 or apply online at the CMC website www.cmc.mlaw.gov.sg. You will need your Singpass to access this e-service                       </div><div> </div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8npa00at124y67t0mpju","title":"Can I sue the other party is he breached the agreement?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8npa00au124y911nzi4b","body":"You can seek legal advice on the types of legal recourse that is available to you.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8npa00av124yemfjvrhh","title":"Do I need to inform my management if I engage CMC to help with an issue with a co-worker?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8npa00aw124yxfasxlku","body":"If you are engaging CMC's mediation service in your private capacity, you do not need to inform your management, unless it is required under your employment contract. All matters that are discussed during a CMC mediation is kept private and confidential.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8npa00ax124yuy27srs6","title":"How do I know if my dispute is suitable for mediation?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8npa00ay124ynext6076","body":"If your dispute is a social, family or community dispute that does not involve legal, contractual and commercial issues, it is likely suitable for mediation at the CMC. Please call us at 1800 2255 529 or visit us at www.cmc.mlaw.gov.sg for more information. <br/><div><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><ol>\n</ol>\n</span></div>","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}},{"id":"cluhz8npa00az124yr8rkiinq","title":"What is CMC?","body":null,"createdAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","published":true,"publishedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:10.459Z","priority":0,"answer":{"id":"cluhz8npa00b0124yojyarlob","body":"The CMC is the Community Mediation Centre. It is set up under the Ministry of Law to provide mediation service to residents in Singapore. It is  located at 45 Maxwell Road #07-11 The URA Centre (East Wing). Its operational hours are from 8.30am to 5pm on weekdays.","updatedAt":"2024-04-02T06:07:11.457Z","numPositiveFeedback":0},"topics":[{"id":703,"title":"Community Mediation","priority":0,"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"parentTopic":null}],"agency":{"code":"mlaw","logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png"}}],"webResult":null,"count":936,"agency":{"id":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","name":"Ministry of Law","code":"mlaw","homepageUrl":"https://www.mlaw.gov.sg","enquiryPageUrl":"https://eservices.mlaw.gov.sg/enquiry/","scope":"GLOBAL","emailDomainWhitelist":[],"type":"SCRAPED","minimumDayResponseTime":3,"responseTimeRange":10,"logoUrl":"https://logos.ask.gov.sg/mlaw.png","searchHint":"Legal Aid, Public Trustee","description":null,"trendingTerms":[],"hasSubjectTriaging":false,"subjects":[]},"currentPage":9,"matchedTokens":null,"agencyTopics":[{"id":729,"qcount":189,"title":"Precious Stones and Precious Metals Dealers","agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","parentTopicId":null,"priority":0,"subtopics":[{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":730,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":53,"title":"Reporting Requirement - Semi-Annual Return"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":1454,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":38,"title":"Regulatory Regime - CTR Filing / CDD matters"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":735,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":36,"title":"Registration and Renewal"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":732,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":17,"title":"Regulatory Regime - Guidance"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":736,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":9,"title":"myPal - Screening Function"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":737,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":8,"title":"myPal"},{"agencyId":"cloxyki9q002d460x58r013fq","id":731,"parentTopicId":729,"priority":0,"qcount":4,"title":"Regulatory Regime - Other Matters"},{"age